vertical-align: middle; does not do what you think it does. It only works for tables or inline / inline-block content.

flex:
flex-grow flex-shrink flex-basis
flex-basis like width
flex-grow and flex-shrink only work with flex-basis
flex-grow will grow when there are more space
flex-shrink bigger flex-basis element faster then others. 

z-index:
work on positioned block

Center in CSS: 
https://css-tricks.com/centering-css-complete-guide/ 

>Horizontal center:
  text-align: center; works for inline, inline-block, inline-table, inline-flex
   margin: 0 auto;: works for block
>vertical center: 
  height: 100px;&&line-height: 100px; works for center text in block.
  vertical-align: middle;
  display: flex; &&justify-content: center; &&flex-direction: column;
>vertical center and horizontal center:
 display: flex;&&justify-content: center;&&align-items: center;
  margin: auto;
  
  
  
